id: pmc-scof
title: Verify release readiness with GitHub npm pm and history checks
description: "Run the current external and local verification matrix: GitHub issues, PRs, Actions, Dependabot alerts, repository settings, npm outdated, npm audit, package dry-run, release gate, clean temporary install, published install after release, and full reachable-history private data scan."
type: Task
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[4]: github,npm,security,verification
created_at: "2026-05-23T22:14:51.767Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-23T22:18:26.671Z"
deadline: "2026-05-24T00:00:00.000Z"
author: codex
estimated_minutes: 90
acceptance_criteria: "- gh CLI confirms repository, issue, PR, workflow, secret, and Dependabot alert state.\\n- npm outdated and npm audit report no actionable issues.\\n- npm run release:check passes.\\n- A clean temporary project installs the local checkout and generates a changelog.\\n- A clean temporary project installs the published npm package after release and generates a changelog.\\n- Reachable git history scan finds no confirmed private data.\\n- Final GitHub release and npm dist-tag are verified."
parent: pmc-t7ie
reviewer: steve
risk: high
confidence: high
sprint: 2026-05-release
release: v2026.05.23-7
resolution: "Completed pre-release GitHub, npm, dependency, vulnerability, release-gate, temp-install, and history privacy checks for v2026.05.23-7."
expected_result: "Release-readiness checks prove the package is buildable, testable, auditable, installable through pm, clean against current GitHub and npm reports, and safe for public release."
actual_result: "GitHub checks confirmed public repository settings, no open issues, no open pull requests, latest CI and Daily Release green, NPM_TOKEN present, and no Dependabot alerts. npm checks found no outdated packages and zero production vulnerabilities, with npm latest 2026.5.23-6 before this release. Local checks passed release:check with 18 tests, included docs in package dry run, and installed locally in /tmp/pm-changelog-v2026-05-23-7-local-QQsBX1 with extension activation ok and smoke changelog generation. History checks matched only documented sanitizer code and synthetic token secret fixtures, and filename scan found no secret-bearing filenames."
